This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning techniques for policy adoption and validation, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on decision-making in aviation safety, which involves control systems and human-computer interaction, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the cost of sequential trials, which could be related to computational complexity, making cs.CY (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category.
